abstract: NEW ENGLAND MASSACHUSETTS: BILINGUAL EDUCATION CHALLENGE Ron Unz, the software millionaire who led successful efforts to end bilingual education in Arizona and California, announced that he planned financial support for a Massachusetts ballot initiative to replace bilingual classes. abstract: SOUTHWEST TEXAS: DALLAS MAYOR RESIGNS TO RUN FOR SENATE Ron Kirk, left, the first black mayor of Dallas, resigned to run for the Senate. Mr. Kirk, a Democrat, will seek the Senate seat being vacated by Phil Gramm, a Republican who is retiring. Mr. Kirk, 47, is expected to face at least three other Democrats in the March 12 primary, among them Representative Ken Bentsen and Dan Morales, the former attorney general of Texas. State Attorney General John Cornyn is expected to be the Republican candidate. Mary Poss, mayor pro tem, succeeds Mr. Kirk as mayor for the remaining two years of his term.Â Â  (AP).
